=== sw-cor24-rpg-ii Minimal RPG-II Demo (Reverse + Third Output Shape) ===
Program:
H  control header
F  input file INFIL
I  field 01: A0110  (10-char input slice)
I  field 02: A0810  (3-char input tail slice)
C  REVR01 -> calc work field
O  DETAIL01 output (10 chars)
O  DETAIL02 output (3 chars)
O  DETAIL03 output (6 chars)

Current boundary:
- Real today: the tiny parsed O-spec subset can now hold a third detail
  output shape, and the runtime can select it for one constrained parsed
  calc case without destabilizing the existing demos.
- This variant composes REVR01 with DETAIL03, so the reversed 10-byte
  field is trimmed to a 6-byte output line.

Current runtime-produced output:
A10 DR
B20 DR
C30 DR

Authored source: rpg2.hlasm
Tiny demo source: tiny_rpg_demo_revr6.src
Generated source: build/rpg2.generated.s
